once if there is a build problem, so that's the first step. So when you are creating the build using Maven, build is not successful, then what is your debugging?

Error 1 — Compilation error:

[ERROR] COMPILATION ERROR
[ERROR] src/main/java/App.java:[10,5] 
        cannot find symbol

Means:
→ Code has syntax error
→ Missing import
→ Wrong method name
→ Developer code issue
→ Not your problem as DevOps
→ Tell developer to fix code ✅

Error 2 — Dependency not found:

[ERROR] Could not resolve dependencies
[ERROR] Could not find artifact
        com.example:library:jar:1.0.0

Means:
→ Maven cant download dependency
→ Check internet connection
→ Check Maven repository
→ Check pom.xml version correct

Fix:
# Check pom.xml
cat pom.xml | grep dependency

# Clear Maven cache and retry
rm -rf ~/.m2/repository
mvn clean install

Error 3 — Repository not reachable:

[ERROR] Failed to connect to repository
[ERROR] Connection refused to
        https://repo.maven.apache.org

Means:
→ No internet access
→ Proxy issue
→ Nexus/Artifactory down

Fix:
# Check internet
curl https://repo.maven.apache.org

# Check proxy settings
cat ~/.m2/settings.xml

# Check Nexus is running
curl http://nexus.company.com:8081

Error 6 — Plugin not found:

[ERROR] Plugin org.apache.maven.plugins:
        maven-compiler-plugin:3.8.1
        not found

Fix:
# Clear plugin cache
rm -rf ~/.m2/repository/org/apache/maven
mvn clean install

Error 7 — Wrong Java version:

[ERROR] Source option 5 is no longer
        supported. Use 6 or later.

Means:
→ Java version mismatch
→ pom.xml says Java 11
→ Server has Java 8

Fix:
# Check Java version
java -version

# Check what pom.xml requires
cat pom.xml | grep java.version

# Install correct Java version
sudo dnf install java-11-amazon-corretto

Full debugging flow:

mvn clean install fails
        │
        ▼
Read error message carefully
        │
        ▼
Identify error type:
├── Compilation  → developer fix
├── Dependency   → clear cache/check repo
├── Repository   → check network/Nexus
├── Test failure → skip or fix test
├── Memory       → increase heap
├── Plugin       → clear cache
└── Java version → install correct JDK
        │
        ▼
Apply fix
        │
        ▼
Run again:
mvn clean install
        │
        ▼
BUILD SUCCESS ✅
