How do you secure secrets in CI/CD pipelines?

Never do this:

# WRONG ❌
pipeline {
    environment {
        DB_PASSWORD = "mypassword123"  ← hardcoded
        API_KEY     = "sk-1234567890"  ← in plain text
    }
}

Problems:
├── Visible in Git history    ❌
├── Anyone can read it        ❌
├── Logs expose it            ❌
└── Security breach risk      ❌
---
Method 1 — Jenkins Credentials Store:

Jenkins Console:
Manage Jenkins
→ Credentials
→ System
→ Global credentials
→ Add Credentials

Type     → Secret text
Secret   → mypassword123
ID       → db-password
--------
// Use in Jenkinsfile
pipeline {
    environment {
        DB_PASSWORD = credentials('db-password')
    }
    stages {
        stage('Deploy') {
            steps {
                sh 'echo $DB_PASSWORD'
                // prints *** in logs ✅
                // never exposed ✅
            }
        }
    }
}
--
For AWS Access Key and Secret Key:

Manage Jenkins
→ Credentials
→ System
→ Global credentials
→ Add Credentials

Kind     → AWS Credentials  ← select this
ID       → aws-credentials
Access Key ID     → AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE
Secret Access Key → wJalrXUtnFEMI/K7MDENG

Use in Jenkinsfile:

pipeline {
    stages {
        stage('Deploy to AWS') {
            steps {
                withAWS(credentials: 'aws-credentials',
                        region: 'us-east-2') {
                    sh 'aws s3 ls'
                    sh 'aws ec2 describe-instances'
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
----------------------------------------------------
Method 2 — AWS Secrets Manager:

Store secrets in AWS:
AWS Console
→ Secrets Manager
→ Store a new secret
→ Key/Value:
   DB_PASSWORD = mypassword123
   API_KEY     = sk-1234567890
→ Name: prod/myapp/secrets

--
// Fetch in pipeline
pipeline {
    stages {
        stage('Get Secrets') {
            steps {
                script {
                    def secret = sh(
                        script: """
                            aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \
                            --secret-id prod/myapp/secrets \
                            --query SecretString \
                            --output text
                        """,
                        returnStdout: true
                    ).trim()
                    // use secret
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

